The paper discusses the automatic generation of metadata for digital resources, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The proposed method leverages associative networks, which are a type of graph-based data structure commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications. The method is also shown to be computationally inexpensive, which is a desirable trait in systems for large-scale data processing and storage (cs.SI).
